i))\n-   nfs: Fix the skip reconcile for nfs daemons ([#&#8203;15909](https://redirect.github.com/rook/rook/issues/15909), [@&#8203;parth-gr](https://redirect.github.com/parth-gr))\n-   nfs: Skip NFS daemon reconciliation when labeled with skip-reconcile ([#&#8203;15889](https://redirect.github.com/rook/rook/issues/15889), [@&#8203;patrostkowski](https://redirect.github.com/patrostkowski))\n-   core: Improve reporting for reconcile requeue cases ([#&#8203;15884](https://redirect.github.com/rook/rook/issues/15884), [@&#8203;OdedViner](https://redirect.github.com/OdedViner))\n-   csi: Enable CSI metadata injection setting by default ([#&#8203;15867](https://redirect.github.com/rook/rook/issues/15867), [@&#8203;OdedViner](https://redirect.github.com/OdedViner))\n-   core: Fix golangci-lint check ST1005 ([#&#8203;15875](https://redirect.github.com/rook/rook/issues/15875), [@&#8203;cbarria](https://redirect.github.com/cbarria))\n-   osd: During PVC resize wait for a short time to restart OSDs ([#&#8203;15824](https://redirect.github.com/rook/rook/issues/15824), [@&#8203;parth-gr](https://redirect.github.com/parth-gr))\n-   rbdmirror: Update mirroring status on pools and rados namespaces for latest ceph changes ([#&#8203;15858](https://redirect.github.com/rook/rook/issues/15858), [@&#8203;parth-gr](https://redirect.github.com/parth-gr))\n-   crd: Allow network provider to be set to blank ([#&#8203;15842](https://redirect.github.com/rook/rook/issues/15842), [@&#8203;yifeng-cerebras](https://redirect.github.com/yifeng-cerebras))\n\n</details>\n\n---\n\n### Configuration\n\n\ud83d\udcc5 **Schedule**: Branch creation - At any time (no schedule defined), Automerge - At any time (no schedule defined).\n\n\ud83d\udea6 **Automerge**: Enabled.\n\n\u267b **Rebasing**: Whenever PR is behind base branch, or you tick the rebase/retry checkbox.\n\n\ud83d\udd15 **Ignore**: Close this PR and you won't be reminded about this update again.\n\n---\n\n - [ ] <!-- rebase-check -->If you want 